@beamer.electronics Well, it's one pole to the other. Ground is still not part of the set.

Lightning can involve ground, since ground may be one of the poles.

As for the discharge current, 0.1 ohm is way off (100-ish to1000-ish ohm for body, also the tube paint is not very conductive), also duration is very short (pF to nF capacitance), thus unable to block stuff(heart/muscles) for extended time.
